<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DOUBLE DIAPHRAGM ANCHORLOK SPRING BRAKE - CAGING SPRING - MECHANICAL RELEASE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
        <title>MECHANICAL RELEASE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To cage the compression spring, tighten release stud nut with a handwrench (DO NOT USE
                IMPACT WRENCH) and make certain push rod is retracting (
                <hotlnk document="s04019_HL0401901.xml" xrefid="f0401908">Figure 8</hotlnk>). Torque the release stud
                nut to 35 lb-ft. (47 N&#8226;m) maximum.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Do not over torque release stud assembly.</para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Over torquing the nut can cause compression spring pressure plate damage.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To ensure compression spring is fully caged, the stud length beyond the nut (
                <hotlnk document="s04019_HL0401901.xml" xrefid="f0401908">Figure 8</hotlnk>) should measure:
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>36 Type Chamber = 3.38" Minimum</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>30 Type Chamber = 2.875" Minimum</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>24 Type Chamber = 2.915" Minimum</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>If the recommended "X" dimension is not correct for chamber size and torque value, the double
                        diaphragm Anchorlok assembly should be considered structurally damaged and should be replaced.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
